children.text:
Career: Appeared in 36 games with 24 starts…has 133 receptions for 1,723 yards and 15 touchdowns…has one fumble return for 18 yards and a touchdown

Honors: 2012 All-SLC Honorable Mention...2013 All-SLC Second Team…SLC Special Teams Player of the Week (9/17/12)

2013: Appeared in 11 games with ten starts as a wide receiver...led the team in receptions (50), receiving yards (721), and receiving touchdowns (7)...returned one punt for 20 yards...finished fifth in the SLC with 4.5 receptions per game and sixth with 65.5 receiving yards per game...caught five passes for 160 yards and two touchdowns against Stephen F. Austin...caught eight passes for 128 yards and a touchdown against Missouri State...named All-SLC Second Team

2012: Appeared in 12 games…had 56 receptions for 616 yards and 6 touchdowns…returned one fumble for 18 yards and a touchdown…ranked second on the team in receptions and third in total receiving yards and receiving yards per game (51.3)…caught six balls for 41 yards and a touchdown against Ole Miss…caught five passes for 63 yards and a touchdown against Northwestern State…caught seven passes for 75 yards and a touchdown against Eastern Illinois…named All-Southland Conference Honorable Mention…named SLC Special Teams Player of the Week on 9/17

2011:  Appeared in 13 games with 2 starts at receiver...had 27 receptions for 386 yards and 2 touchdowns...scored touchdowns against Stephen F. Austin and Nicholls State

High School: Two-year letterman in football and basketball for North Mesquite High School...2010 All-District selection...2010 team MVP/Stallion Award...19 receptions, 497 yards, 5 TDs, 26.2 yards per catch...member of National Honor Society
